entry.title: Linked Open Karnak Temples Bibliography: 1986-2012
entry.content:
Linked Open Karnak Temples Bibliography: 1743-1920 | 1921-1985 | 1986-2012


Photograph of the temple complex taken in 1914 - Cornell University Library


On 9 May 2012 I noted the appearance online of the Karnak Temples Bibliography:  CFEETK Online Bibliographical Project.

I abstract below the linked open component of that bibliography accessible as of 17 May 2012.  All 814 items on this list should be available from AWOL in full text to anyone having a network connection and access to Google services - AWOL operates on Blogger, which is a Google product. If google services are restricted at your location go directly to CFEETK Online Bibliographical Project.

Entries marked with a green bullet ( = 506 items) are openly available from CFEETK. 
Entries marked with a yellow bullet ( = 308 items) are openly available elsewhere.  
For the remainder of the bibliography, follow the link to CFEETK Online Bibliographical Project.  That list includes an additional 129 items available digitally, but behind a subscription firewall.

All told, 47% of the 2005 reference in the bibliography are available digitally.  Just over 40% of the full 2005 references are available in open access.  The institutions and individuals who have exposed this scholarship to the world are to be congratulated!
